{"key":"processedPost-16435107","value":{"id":16435107,"first":16430754,"last":16435107,"when":1340641049,"utime":"06/25/12 07:17 PM","cleanedPost":"The grains should not have been placed on the perlite.&nbsp; The perlite is only to supply humidity.&nbsp; By placing grains on perlite, they're attempting to colonize it, but there is no food source there.<br />If you want to fruit grains, you're supposed to put the fully colonized grains in a tray, and then place your casing layer over that, and then set the tray above the perlite.&nbsp; Even better is to mix the colonized grains with a bulk substrate such as manure, and then fruit it either cased or uncased.&nbsp; Take a look at the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Horse-Manure-Substrate\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">manure preparation video</a> to see how the latter is done.&nbsp; You'll also find a casing layer preparation video and the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">shotgun terrarium fruiting chamber</a> tek at the same place.&nbsp; Good luck.<br />RR"}}